{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, most state-of-the-art image captioning methods now utilize Transformer-based architectures.",
    "Zhu et al. [45] first proposed a CNN-Transformer framework.",
    "However, by only using global image features as input to the decoder, this method fails to capture finegrained contextual details, instead encoding irrelevant information that yields inaccurate and verbose captions.",
    "To address these limitations, Xian et al. [39] propose a Transformer-based method that optimizes region feature representations in the encoding stage using mesh features and geometric information.",
    "Wang et al. [37] pioneer the use of Swin Transformers as encoders for image captioning, helping to address prior limitations in this field."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Zhu et al. [45] first proposed a CNN-Transformer framework.",
    "To address these limitations, Xian et al. [39] propose a Transformer-based method that optimizes region feature representations in the encoding stage using mesh features and geometric information.",
    "Wang et al. [37] pioneer the use of Swin Transformers as encoders for image captioning, helping to address prior limitations in this field."
